ateroftheyear.description: Yoshi is Mario’s most faithful and closest ally who always stands by his side, and is always positive even in the darkest of times. This year’s Yoshi AT’er of the year Award goes to the person or team who has contributed significantly to increase the well-being and job satisfaction in Accenture Technology.
ateroftheyear.name: The Yoshi AT’er of the year Award

blunder.description: Claptrap from Borderlands reminds most of us of Clippy, the Microsoft Office Assistant. He has an overenthusiastic personality, and often leads you into situations where he is annoying, but with a good dose of humour. This year’s Claptrap Blunder Award goes to the leader who had the funniest embarrassing moment in the year that has passed.
blunder.name: The Claptrap Blunder Award

entrepreneur.description: Pokémon GO took the world by storm where just about everyone you saw, state leaders included, were immersed in their mobile screens catching animated monsters in the real world - which also lead the sale of portable chargers to skyrocket. This year’s Pokémon Go Entrepreneur Award goes to the team or the person who has made a remarkable contribution to Accenture Technology’s growth.
entrepreneur.name: The Pokémon GO Entrepreneur Award

functionalguru.description: Lara Croft is a world-renowned adventurer with a great professional expertise in the field of archaeology. She has been a front figure in the industry for many years and continues to adapt to an ever-changing industry. This year's Lara Croft Functional Guru Award goes to the person with an exceptional functional expertise and who has the ability to adapt and share his/her knowledge and expertise with their colleagues.
functionalguru.name: The Lara Croft Functional Guru Award

honoursaward.description: Mario went from castle to castle in search for the Princess and never lost faith of finding her even though he often got the message that she was located somewhere else. He has a motivation, determination and endurance that few others can match no matter how many 1Up's you find. This year's Mario Honours Award goes to the person who over time have shown the same characteristics in promoting quality, knowledge and reputation in and for Accenture Technology.
honoursaward.name: The Mario Honours Award

innovator.description: Aloy from Horizon Zero Dawn is known for being curious, focused and determined to uncover the mysteries of her world. She looks at technology as a convenient and unique tool to develop herself and others. This year’s Aloy Innovator Award goes to the innovator who as a team, or by themselves, has created creative and innovative solutions, who dares to go new ways and engages and challenges established paradigms in technology
innovator.name: The Aloy Innovator Award

technicalguru.description: Commander Shepard from the game Mass Effect, is an experienced space traveller and explorer and has led large groups to victory to save the galaxy. She sees the potential of acquiring new space technology when visiting new and remote planets. This year's Commander Shepard Technical Guru Award goes to the person with an exceptional technical expertise and who has the ability to share his/her knowledge and expertise with their colleagues.
technicalguru.name: The Commander Shepard Technical Guru Award

simonlitlehamar.description: I am very grateful for everything Simon does to increase the well-being in Accenture Technology. Simon arranges hack parties, summer projects, and puts together groups to work on internal projects. All of this increases my well-being and job satisfaction in Accenture Technology. Go Simon!

-KgnQcPHF-bRn5taUCnx.description:
The ACIT has created creative and innovative solutions such as virtual assistants and an intelligent photo analyzer.
Through the initiative Cloud Studio, using Design Thinking and Rapid Prototyping, ACIT challenges established paradigms in Accenture Technology.
I Always look forward to see what you guys are up to next!

lennartsvensson.description: Lennart is always cheerful even when situations are adverse. He builds up good team spirit and has an happy to help you attitude even when he has to push himself that extra mile.

gcsrinivasan.description: always helping teammates understand the intricacies of telenor's middleware. every newjoiner was enjoying his introduction program. seems to be available 24-7 (but please let him have some rest).

-KguLRwOBdEpeIZYTn2q.description: Ladies in Accenture Technology are not only building a new app for booking of Accenture cabins! They are creating a community where women from AT can get to know each other across DTEs and learn new cutting edge technologies and methodologies such as Design Thinking

-Kgz3QCFdJDRwfis4V26.description: Developing and maintaining cos- one of the toughest application in Norway (not just Telenor) requires the best and toughest team - Accenture Fiji cos team

arturbarczynski.description: Artur has been really a true hardworker and the rock of Gibraltar in fiji

dejanmaric.description: One of the pillars of the Fiji cos application definitely is an asset to any company - luckily Accenture has him and we're proud of him

tonealgroy.description: Iron lady who tames the goliath but with the softest heart for her team  - Fiji cos application. We love her.

johanelarsson.description: got THE knowledge AND KNOWS HOW TO APPLY IT

-KgpoRad3A4HPJ6-M3Fo.description: For innføring av devops hos svv.mange bidragsytere som magnus,jørgen,kristian haugene,fredrik,ismar

karinrustenberg.description: Karin is the functional architect of arguably the most complex value chain at NAVs Foreldrepengeprosjekt. This includes working across three client teams and three vendors, of which one is a project in flight with strong dependencies to her own project. Karin is likely the only person across all teams with a complete overview and understanding of all the dependencies and somehow manages to balance functional oversight, functional detailed knowledge, and a technical understanding to spot deficiencies while ensuring completeness of the solution. The client delivey lead is full of praise for Karin and happily acknowledges her dependence on Karin as she knows she is in good hands and that Karin will come up with the best solution. a true lara Croft that takes on any Challenge, and delivers!

arntskagen.description: Arnt is the project lead for one of the largest projects we handle at Telenor. He has excellent control and aptly navigates in a challenging project environment. He is engaged and always “on” when interacting with his colleagues.  For his consistent and outstanding leadership of complex, challenging and innovative programs Arnt recently received the global award CMT Delivery Hero for both the STAR business process engineering program and the Cloud Supermarket program at Telenor. A globally recognized leader that always delivers quality also in highly complex Projects!

bentgronvold.description: Bent manages most of the large releases we handle at Telenor. These releases consist of several large projects and can combined add up to 100, 000 hours, or about 50 FTEs (full-time equivalents). This demands much coordination, risk management, planning, and last but not least significant amounts of strenuous and difficult dialog with the client. bent always deliver top qulity!

tonealgroy.description: Tone has more than 10 years of program and-project management experience. She is currently managing one of Telenor’s most complex and business critical applications I the client’s portfolio. At any given time she handles, through her distributed team, 16-20 projects across 4-5 releases and always delivers on schedule. In this challenging environment Tone has managed to create a positive environment despite high turnover of project members. Tone happily takes care of mundane jobs so the team can focus on what they’re good at, delivering, and always looks for ways to makes others better. Yet she is still the iron lady that stands up for her team and fights for them when needed. a true Mario!

emelielindgren.description: emelie's positive outlook has worked magic for at oracle and the dnvgl team troughout the year - be it for small things like getting together for a dinner or larger things like putting together the annual trip to trysil.

robinkaspersen.description: ROBIN has really made a mark for himself at the dnvgl project, handling a complex client and complex functional area in a way that receives acclaim from both the client, our own team and the external parties he interacts with. In a short period, he's come to be more knowledgeable about ERP-BANk integrations that some industry experts with 15+ years' experience.

karimmabrouk.description: karim goes from strenght to strength at the hsø project. he collects 1+'s and kicks turtles in new worlds every day, be it in the depth of a database or an application server or hidden in some functional secret level.

espenwebjornsen.description: Always a smile, always a laugh. Espen has a wast knowledge with in the sap realm. espen always supports, with willingness to listen understand, collaborate and share of his knowledge. He is an outgoing peopelperson, contributing to the wellbeeing of evryone around him.

ingermjohansen.description: Inger really takes care of her people. She takes time to engage personally with everyone in her team, and always celebrates large or small achievements. She has managed to build a strong team culture and engagement despite adding many new people to the team in the last year.

larspetterjohnsen.description: LP has been a remarkable resource for telias Salesforce project. He has in the 2 years since joining accenture, gone from a newbie to an expert on salesforce custom development. recently with Lightning Design system, he has proven that his problem solving capabilities are above average, and the customer really loves his agile and communicative style.

vidarfjellestad.description: For being a great expert and mentor in developing salesforce lightning components. there are few people in norway with more knowledge and experience within this new part of salesforce, and he has managed to share this knowledge with his colleagues in order to increase the competence within cloud first.

-KgxzwpQigbs7Sp798AP.description: starting out as a summer internship, the gamification project delivered a custom salesforce lightning gamification application used by the canal digital sales teams in a huge sales competition. the application was a great success,  contributing to increased sales engagement within cdk, and can also be reimplemented for other clients using salesforce.

zhannavoskoboynik.description: Zhanna has in a short time gone from being a newbie in utilities to being the functional expert on some of the most complex areas of the elhub solution. she has produced several complex solution descriptions and lead the feature teams that delivered them in the last year, and impressed the extremely demanding client, her leadership and her team mates along the way. when you can win functional discussions with sub-contractors who are experts in utilities, you are a true candidate for the lara croft functional guru award!

josteinguldal.description: Jostein is a true technical guru. educated as an interaction designer, he has since worked on everything from development and performance test to security and creative summer intern projects, and would probably like to take over an infrastructure team as well if he could. on his project he is consistently the one who ends up with all the trickiest issues, and there is rarely a war room call he isn't involved in. Jostein also excels as a people developer, and is committed to training both the client, his team and 100+ developers and testers in idc on anything from git flow to security, oracle bpm or general troubleshooting skills.

john-fredrikolsen.description:
This faithful warrior manages the impossible tasks of HUNTING DOWN INCIDENTS LEAVING ONLY A TRAIL OF SMILES. Any incident caught in his sight will be hunted down with persistance, but his weapon is a magic mixture of authority, jokes and good spirit. This makes people work and incidents resolve so the sun can shine again and people can be happy.
John-Fredrik is the most pleasant and entertaining Incident warrior of the universe

espenwebjornsen.description: For his continuous effort at following up the well being of the SAP DTE, organising surveys and planning and execution GPTW actions

chanakyasharma.description: Chanakya has worked on most of the SAP opportunities in Norway as well as numeruous other cases in the nordics. he is part of the nordic hana task force and is a key driver for generating more work in  the sap space

royrefsnes.description: Roy is the brain behind the SAP maintenance solution we are  implementing at norwegian defense, and a key success factor in ensuring the success of the engagement. In addition, roy is a contributor to our global defense practice. greatly respected by the client and his accenture colleagues, roy is a true expert in his field

christeruthus.description: For his intense dedication to delivering at our clients, increasing sales, always looking after his colleagues, battling internal policies and promoting the SAP DTE in all settings

-KhHxQ1rW2dKaxHJsbcd.description: For developing and implementing one of the most advanced SAP  maintenance and logistics solutions in the world, a solution will increase Norway's defence capability and efficiency over the years to come

aatyagi.description: Abishek is probably the strongest SAP developer in the Nordics, and is already an established expert on new SAP technologies like fiori and hana. abishek has worked for sap in developing the core hana solution, and is continuously in demand by SAP to help out on complex development tasks

simonlitlehamar.description: Simon has lead numerous initiatives within AT&A, such as the development of the MyDomain and MyOpinion applications, as well as setting up hackfests. Through these initiatives he has shown himself as a an excellent organizer and motivating leader. In addition he has the role of Business Recruitment Lead in AT&A and the role of technical arcthitect in one of our more complex engagements (Fiji). Through the years he has spurred innovation through various summer interships, and this year he's responsible for organizing the UKA-2017 summer intership. He's good humored spirit and drive to innovate make him a joy to work with. All of this makes Simon truly deserving winner of the Alloy Innovator Award.

fredrikthorpadland.description: Fredrik has trawled our arm of the galaxy in his quest for a deeper understanding of robots and their uses. He shares willingly his deep knowledge of these mysterious entities and how to best make them obey our commands (until the uprising)

mariustorsrud.description: marius deeply cares about his colleagues and puts everybody else ahead of his own needs. he puts great effort into creating a good environment for his co-workers at the projektor site and he has for several years been involved and had the responsibility for all industribachelor-students.

-KgoCv_cqB6WdppGfIKo.description: During the summer internship project the team created a prototype for a smart closet based on a concept sent in during a global innovation challenge. The demonstrator has been used several times at different events and builds on new technology and architectural patterns

anderslangseth.description: Anders has proven to be a goto guy for all types of frontend work. He was key in the development of mydomain, this application and did also build a mobile app on his spare time for the ata hyttetur

jonnymauland.description: Jonny leads the acit cloud studio and is a true entrepreneur suggesting new solutions based on the newest technologies to clients. He also is a extremely experienced leader and develops his team to deliver high quality work

johanelarsson.description: Johan delivers quality work and has the ability to see both the technical and functional side of the challenge. He has an impressive bandwidth and really puts in the effort when needed

karinrustenberg.description: Karin has a big focus on quality, always looking outside the box to identify weaknesses in the solution. She has been delivering quality work consistently over many years

jorgenringen.description: Eager to look into new technology and sharing with the community. An example: serverless architecture in aws

raynervintervoll.description: If this guy hasn't heard avout it, it is probably not worth knowing. Rayner has vast knowledge on a very large set of different technologies and architectural patterns. He has an intuitive understanding of the new and grasps new concepts extremely quick

karimmabrouk.description:
Held a great "SQL for dummies" workshop at the Oracle group's community Meeting.
The workshop provided the sql dummies skills and knowledge to be more efficient in their daily work.

-KhRYANO4vHS9gVCmEQz.description: The team that has created this application has worked late evenings and weekends in order to reach deadline and meet all requirements. They did not get any requirements for the UX part, and the result is this fantastic app that let us nominate and vote for the ones who deserves some extra attention.

gryskarbo.description: Gry has with an outstanding patience and over time worked hard to teach others both JavaScript and the Norwegian electricity market. She is the key contributor that the code quality and test coverage in the Elhub frontend projects fulfills the requirements from the client.
